        <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
         <a href="/news/article-9318245/Texas-lifts-COVID-19-precautions-including-mask-mandate-restrictions-businesses.html" itemprop="url">
          Texas and Mississippi lift ALL their COVID restrictions: Both GOP governors say 'it's time to reopen', end their mask mandates and remove limits on businesses crippled by the pandemic
         </a>
        </h2>
        <a href="/news/article-9318245/Texas-lifts-COVID-19-precautions-including-mask-mandate-restrictions-businesses.html">
         <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/5274236145022909316/308x174_JPG_5274236145022909316.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="70" data-frame-height="178" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/5274236145022909316/636x382_JPG-HD_5274236145022909316.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="70" data-hd-frame-height="370" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/5274236145022909316/964x580_JPG-SINGLE_5274236145022909316.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/5274236145022909316/964x580_MP4_5274236145022909316.mp4" height="562" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="964"/>
         <noscript>
          <img height="562" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/5274236145022909316/964x580_JPG-SINGLE_5274236145022909316.jpg" width="964"/>
         </noscript>
        </a>
        <div class="articletext">
         <div>
          <p>
           Texas is lifting its mask mandate, Gov Greg Abbott (top right, inset) said Tuesday, making it the largest state to end an order intended to prevent the spread of the coronavirus that has killed more than 42,000 Texans beginning on March 10, as Mississippi's governor says residents can go back to their normal lives as soon as tomorrow. Abbott has faced sharp criticism from his party over the mandate, which was imposed eight months ago, and other COVID-19 restrictions. It was only ever lightly enforced, even during the worst outbreaks of the pandemic. Texas will also do away with limits on the number of diners that businesses can serve indoors, said Abbott, who made the announcement at a restaurant in Lubbock. Abbott later tweeted: 'I just announced Texas is OPEN 100%. EVERYTHING. I also ended the statewide mask mandate.' Mississippi immediately followed Texas' decision. Mississippi Gov Tate Reeves (bottom inset right) tweeted Tuesday afternoon: 'Starting tomorrow, we are lifting all of our county mask mandates and businesses will be able to operate at full capacity without any state-imposed rules. Mississippi reported 301 new infections and 44 deaths on Tuesday. The state has recorded a total of 295,295, infections and 6,724 deaths. Texas and Mississippi joined other states in easing coronavirus restrictions, despite warnings from health experts that the pandemic is far from over.
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>

         </h6>

      <div class="cleared lead-alpha">
       <div class="alpha">
        <div class="column-splitter">
         <div class="column-split first-column">
          <div class="article article-large cleared" data-original-title="New York state legislators reach deal to RESCIND Cuomo's emergency powers">
           <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
            <a href="/news/article-9318675/New-York-state-legislators-reach-deal-RESCIND-Cuomos-emergency-powers.html">
             'Creepy' Cuomo under pressure to quit with huge billboard erected telling him to resign after the Emmy-award winning Gov who boasted about his handling of the pandemic in book is stripped of his emergency COVID powers
            </a>
           </h2>
           <a href="/news/article-9318675/New-York-state-legislators-reach-deal-RESCIND-Cuomos-emergency-powers.html">
            <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/818734039252252766/308x174_JPG_818734039252252766.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="70" data-frame-height="308" data-frame-width="172" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/818734039252252766/636x382_JPG-HD_818734039252252766.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="70" data-hd-frame-height="636" data-hd-frame-width="356" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/818734039252252766/308x174_JPG-SINGLE_818734039252252766.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/818734039252252766/308x174_MP4_818734039252252766.mp4" height="550" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="308"/>
            <noscript>
             <img height="550" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/818734039252252766/308x174_JPG-SINGLE_818734039252252766.jpg" width="308"/>
            </noscript>
           </a>
           <div class="articletext-holder">
            <p>
             Cuomo was granted the emergency powers on March 3, 2020, and they were due to expire on April 30 this year. On Tuesday a deal was reached to rescind them early, given the fact that the pandemic appears to be steadily being brought under control. Politicians in Albany are also conscious of the scandals surrounding Cuomo - both with a coverup of nursing home COVID deaths, and with three women accusing him of sexual harassment. Cuomo's powers will be removed following a vote in the state legislature - possibly as soon as Friday.
            </p>

        <div class="article article-tri-headline" itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem">
         <meta content="8" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9317781/Prices-six-Dr-Seuss-books-skyrocket-online.html" itemprop="url">
           'I will never cancel Dr Seuss': Fans drive prices of author's books up by hundreds amid outrage over 'woke' decision to pull six titles because of 'racist and insensitive imagery'
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/news/article-9317781/Prices-six-Dr-Seuss-books-skyrocket-online.html">
           <img alt="Prices of six Dr. Seuss books skyrocket online" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/22/39959998-0-image-m-15_1614723695393.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="Prices of six Dr. Seuss books skyrocket online" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/22/39959998-0-image-m-15_1614723695393.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            Dr. Seuss Enterprises, the company that preserves and protects the author's legacy, announced early Tuesday that the six books would no longer be published because they contain racist and insensitive imagery. The six books that will no longer be printed are: 'And to Think That I Saw It on Mulberry Street', 'If I Ran the Zoo', 'McElligot's Pool', 'On Beyond Zebra!', 'Scrambled Eggs Super!', and 'The Cat's Quizzer'. Almost immediately after the announcement, the prices of those books surged hundreds of dollars on eBay as people placed dozens of bids for new and vintage copies. A vintage copy of 'If I Ran the Zoo' was priced at $510 after receiving 54 bids, while a copy of 'Scrambled Eggs Super!' was at $565 after 58 bids. A copy of 'The Cat's Quizzer', which the seller marketed as brand new, was going for $630 after receiving 48 bids. It came as outrage grew on social media among those who said Dr. Seuss was being 'canceled'. Their anger was also directed at President Biden after he omitted Dr. Seuss from Read Across America Day, which is held annually on the children's author's birthday on March 2.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>

           DEFEATING CORONAVIRUS

        <div class="article article-tri-headline">
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/tvshowbiz/article-9318617/Dolly-Parton-75-receives-COVID-19-vaccination-pledging-1M-help-fund-trials.html">
           'Dolly Parton gets a dose of her own medicine': Country star, 75, whose $1million donation to COVID research helped fund the Moderna vaccine gets her first shot and sings 'vaccine, vaccine' to the tune of her hit song 'Jolene'
          </a>
         </h2>
         <a href="/tvshowbiz/article-9318617/Dolly-Parton-75-receives-COVID-19-vaccination-pledging-1M-help-fund-trials.html">
          <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4662319264171274842/308x174_JPG_4662319264171274842.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="70" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4662319264171274842/636x382_JPG-HD_4662319264171274842.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="70" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4662319264171274842/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_4662319264171274842.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4662319264171274842/636x382_MP4_4662319264171274842.mp4" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="636"/>
          <noscript>
           <img height="382" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4662319264171274842/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_4662319264171274842.jpg" width="636"/>
          </noscript>
         </a>
         <div class="articletext">
          <div>
           <p>
            Dolly Parton received a Moderna COVID-19 vaccine on Tuesday after pledging $1million of her own money to help fund trials in April last year. The 75-year-old country music icon posted a picture of herself getting the injection, with a caption that read: 'Dolly gets a dose of her own medicine.' 'Hey it's me!' Parton said in a video posted to her Twitter account. 'I am finally going to get my vaccine, I'm so excited. I've been waiting a while and I'm old enough to get it. So I'm very happy to say I'm going to get my Moderna shot.'
           </p>

           <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
            <a href="/health/article-9317897/U-S-trial-COVID-19-blood-plasma-halted-no-benefit-found.html" itemprop="url">
             NIH halts trial testing blood plasma in more than 500 patients with mild to moderate COVID-19 after finding it did NOT help them recover more quickly
            </a>
           </h2>
           <div class="articletext">
            <a href="/health/article-9317897/U-S-trial-COVID-19-blood-plasma-halted-no-benefit-found.html">
             <img alt="" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/23/39968842-0-image-a-76_1614727163155.jpg" height="115" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="154"/>
             <noscript>
              <img alt="" height="115" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/23/39968842-0-image-a-76_1614727163155.jpg" width="154"/>
             </noscript>
            </a>
            <p>
             On Tuesday, the NIH said it was halting a trial looking at convalescent blood plasma in treating patients with mild-to-moderate coronavirus after an independent board found no benefit.
            </p>
           </div>
           <div class="article-icon-links-container" data-followbutton="MailOnline">
            <ul class="article-icon-links cleared">
             <li class="first">

         <div class="column-split">
          <div class="article article-small" itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem">
           <meta content="13" itemprop="position"/>
           <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
            <a href="/health/article-9316837/States-start-reopen-despite-expert-warnings-case-declines-stalled.html" itemprop="url">
             States from Massachusetts to Missouri relax more COVID restrictions: Vaccinations near 77 million and daily cases stall at 65K - but health officials warn relaxing rules could lead to a FOURTH surge
            </a>
           </h2>
           <div class="articletext">
            <a href="/health/article-9316837/States-start-reopen-despite-expert-warnings-case-declines-stalled.html">
             <img alt="" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/16/39951758-0-image-a-29_1614701656924.jpg" height="115" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="154"/>
             <noscript>
              <img alt="" height="115" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/16/39951758-0-image-a-29_1614701656924.jpg" width="154"/>
             </noscript>
            </a>
            <p>
             Massachusetts on Monday made it much easier to grab dinner and a show.In Missouri, where individual communities get to make the rules, the two biggest metropolitan areas are relaxing some measures.
            </p>

         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9317987/Biden-invoke-Defense-Production-Act-assist-Merck-Johnson-Johnson-vaccine-partnership.html">
           Biden says US is on track to have enough vaccines for every adult by the end of MAY - two months earlier than expected - and invokes Defense Production Act to speed up production of Johnson &amp; Johnson's one-dose shot
          </a>
         </h2>
         <a href="/news/article-9317987/Biden-invoke-Defense-Production-Act-assist-Merck-Johnson-Johnson-vaccine-partnership.html">
          <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/2421854912744409338/308x174_JPG_2421854912744409338.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="52" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/2421854912744409338/636x382_JPG-HD_2421854912744409338.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="52" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/2421854912744409338/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_2421854912744409338.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/2421854912744409338/636x382_MP4_2421854912744409338.mp4" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="636"/>
          <noscript>
           <img height="382" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/2421854912744409338/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_2421854912744409338.jpg" width="636"/>
          </noscript>
         </a>
         <div class="articletext">
          <div>
           <p>
            President Joe Biden said Tuesday that the U.S. will have enough vaccine for every adult in the country by the end of May. Biden made the announcement on the heels of green-lighting the Defense Production Act to be usedto assist Merck with manufacturing Johnson &amp; Johnson's COVID-19 vaccine.
           </p>

            </a>
           </h2>
           <div class="articletext">
            <a href="/health/article-9318271/Nearly-state-saw-sharp-declines-birth-rates-pandemic-began.html">

        <div class="article article-tri-headline" itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem">
         <meta content="19" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9317541/At-12-people-dead-multiple-vehicle-crash-California.html" itemprop="url">
           At least 13 dead and several including children injured after Ford SUV 'with 25 immigrants crammed inside' crashes into a gravel truck near the Mexican border in California
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/news/article-9317541/At-12-people-dead-multiple-vehicle-crash-California.html">
           <img alt="13 'undocumented migrants' dead and several injured after SUV 'carrying 25' crashes into" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/21/39965732-0-image-m-12_1614722188427.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="13 'undocumented migrants' dead and several injured after SUV 'carrying 25' crashes into" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/21/39965732-0-image-m-12_1614722188427.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            The crash occurred on State Route 115 in the area of El Centro, 10 miles north of the US-Mexico border, at around 6:15am local time, authorities said. The SUV, a maroon Ford Expedition said to be carrying 25 passengers, had been driving westbound on Norrish Road when it traveled 'in the direct path' of a gravel truck heading northbound on 115. Twelve people were found dead at the scene, including the driver of the Ford, and another victim died after arriving at El Centro Regional Medical Center, California Highway Patrol Chief Omar Watson said. An area hospital had initially said at least 15 had died, but CHP later clarified the numbers. Several other passengers of the SUV were also hurt, including an undisclosed number of children. At least five of the injured were airlifted from the scene, three of whom are currently in intensive care at the trauma center of Desert Regional Medical Center in Palm Springs. The dead include some Mexican citizens, officials said, who ranged in age between 20 and 55. The injured, meanwhile, are aged between 16 and 55.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>

            </a>
           </h2>
           <div class="articletext">
            <a href="/news/article-9317853/Kayleigh-McEnany-joins-Fox-News-air-contributor.html">
             <img alt="" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/18/39959376-0-image-a-44_1614711116414.jpg" height="115" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="154"/>
             <noscript>

             </noscript>
            </a>
            <p>
             Former White House press secretary Kayleigh McEnany is joining Fox News as an on air contributor. White House press secretary Jen Psaki wished McEnany well in her new gig.
            </p>
           </div>
           <div class="article-icon-links-container" data-followbutton="MailOnline">
            <ul class="article-icon-links cleared">
             <li class="first">

         <meta content="22" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9317067/Obama-initially-refused-support-Joe-Biden-aging-politician-having-hurrah.html" itemprop="url">
           Biden's 'best friend' Obama initially refused to support a 'tragicomic caricature of an aging politician having his last hurrah' and only coronavirus saved him after doing almost everything wrong, new book claims
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/news/article-9317067/Obama-initially-refused-support-Joe-Biden-aging-politician-having-hurrah.html">
           <img alt="Barack Obama initially refused to back Joe Biden, new book claims" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/17/39955592-0-image-a-38_1614704664996.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="Barack Obama initially refused to back Joe Biden, new book claims" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/17/39955592-0-image-a-38_1614704664996.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            A new book claims Joe Biden did almost everything wrong during the 2020 election and ran a lethargic campaign that nearly went bankrupt. The authors claim he was only able to win the presidency due to Donald Trump's mishandling of the Covid-19 pandemic. Top Biden adviser Anita Dunn said that 'Covid was the best thing that happened to him' because it covered up his failings. The claims are in 'Lucky: How Joe Biden Barely Won the Presidency' by Jonathan Allen and Amie Parnes. Barack Obama refused to support Biden even though he served as his Vice President for eight years, the authors write. Obama reportedly feared Biden was a 'tragicomic caricature of an aging politician having his last hurrah'.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>

         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9318363/Bill-Burr-voices-support-fired-Mandalorian-star-Gina-Carano.html">
           Bill Burr voices support for fired Mandalorian co-star Gina Carano calling her as an 'absolute sweetheart' and slamming woke critics who were 'waiting in the weeds' to cancel the conservative actress
          </a>
         </h2>
         <a href="/news/article-9318363/Bill-Burr-voices-support-fired-Mandalorian-star-Gina-Carano.html">
          <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/3256585444382849650/308x174_JPG_3256585444382849650.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="38" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/3256585444382849650/636x382_JPG-HD_3256585444382849650.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="38" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/3256585444382849650/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_3256585444382849650.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/3256585444382849650/636x382_MP4_3256585444382849650.mp4" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="636"/>
          <noscript>
           <img height="382" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/3256585444382849650/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_3256585444382849650.jpg" width="636"/>
          </noscript>
         </a>
         <div class="articletext">
          <div>
           <p>
            Bill Burr is speaking out in support of his conservative Mandalorian co-star Gina Carano, three weeks after she was fired from the Disney+ series for expressing her political views. The 38-year-old actress was let go by bosses on February 11 after she shared a social media post comparing the current political climate to that of Nazi Germany. Fans of Carano claim she is a victim of cancel culture at the hands of a small, vocal 'woke mob' - and many have come to her defense.
           </p>

            </a>
           </h2>
           <div class="articletext">

            </a>
            <p>
             According to anonymous industry sources cited by CNN, Stephanopoulos was irate when Muir was given the responsibility of leading the network'sspecial coverage of breaking news stories.

        <div class="article article-tri-headline" itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem">
         <meta content="28" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9318683/More-1000-people-Kentucky-evacuated-rising-floodwaters-bursting-dam.html" itemprop="url">
           More than 1,000 people in Kentucky are evacuated over fears a dam could BURST as heavy rains see the worst flooding in the area for 60 YEARS
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/news/article-9318683/More-1000-people-Kentucky-evacuated-rising-floodwaters-bursting-dam.html">
           <img alt="More than 1000 people in Kentucky have been evacuated due to rising floodwaters from" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/03/00/39972012-0-image-m-2_1614732193848.jpg" height="620" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="More than 1000 people in Kentucky have been evacuated due to rising floodwaters from" height="620" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/03/00/39972012-0-image-m-2_1614732193848.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            Floodwaters hit several Kentucky counties as weary officials and residents prepared to take stock of the damage to homes, businesses and roads while some were even evacuated. Significant flooding occurred in several Eastern Kentucky counties, where one county official said the high water was the worst since 1957. There were 49 local declarations of disaster across the state as of Tuesday. Five inches of rain was also dumped on parts of Arkansas, Tennessee, West Virginia and Maryland, leaving residents stranded, roads washed out and buildings flooded. Thunderstorms also brought damaging winds to Kentucky, Tennessee, Alabama and Mississippi, knocking down power lines and trees.
           </p>
          </div>

           Tiger Woods' ex-wife Elin Nordegren is seen for the first time since golfer's near-fatal car crash as she takes their two children to soccer practice in Florida
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/news/article-9317885/Tiger-Woods-ex-wife-Elin-Nordegren-seen-time-golfers-near-fatal-car-crash.html">
           <img alt="Tiger Woods' ex-wife Elin Nordegren is seen for the first time since golfer's near-fatal" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/19/39959908-0-image-a-25_1614714146771.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>

           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            Tiger Woods' ex-wife and two children have been pictured out for the first time since his near-fatal car crash last week. Elin Nordegren, 41, was spotted at soccer practice in Palm Beach, Florida on Saturday, with daughter Charlie, 13, and son, Sam, 11 - four days after the golf legend rolled his luxury SUV down a ravine just outside of Los Angeles. The trio were accompanied byNordegren's new husband, ex-NFL star Jordan Cameron, 32, and their 17-month-old son, Arthur, on the outing.
           </p>

           The couple that sweats together...! A smiling Ivanka Trump and Jared Kushner go for a run in scorching Miami heat after former First Daughter's quick trip back to New York City
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/femail/article-9318193/Ivanka-Trump-Jared-Kushner-jogging-Miami-heat.html">
           <img alt="Ivanka Trump and Jared Kushner go jogging together in the Miami heat" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/20/39963290-0-image-a-146_1614718269913.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="Ivanka Trump and Jared Kushner go jogging together in the Miami heat" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/20/39963290-0-image-a-146_1614718269913.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            Ivanka, 39, and Jared, 40, were pictured jogging together on Saturday, when temperatures reached 79 degrees Fahrenheit, days after the mother-of-three was pictured in New York City, where she spent time at Trump Tower, and with her mom Ivana. The couple are avid runners and have been seen working out together multiple times since moving to Miami - a tradition that they also shared while living in Washington, D.C. Ivanka dressed in all-black for their fitness session, pairing leggings with a figure-hugging vest and an all-black New York Mets baseball cap, while Jared wore a plain cap, a grey T-shirt, and patterned shorts. The couple relocated to Florida after former President Donald Trump's exit from the White House, and are currently residing in an exclusive oceanfront building called Arte Surfside. Last weekend, the couple spent a day on a charter yacht in Biscayne Bay with their three children, Arabella, Joseph, and Theodore, and Jared's father Charles Kushner. Charles, 66, was jailed for 14 months in 2005 after pleading guilty to 18 counts of tax evasion, witness tampering, and making illegal campaign donations, but was given a full pardon by Trump in 2020.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>

         <div class="gradient-split wocc link-wocc linkro-wocc">
          <h6>
           HARRY AND MEGHAN AT WAR WITH PALACE
          </h6>
          <div>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="article article-tri-headline" itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem">
         <meta content="37" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/femail/article-9318273/Did-Meghan-Markle-style-inspiration-Wallis-Simpson-Oprah-interview.html" itemprop="url">
           Did Meghan Markle take style inspiration from Wallis Simpson for her Oprah interview? Viewers compare Duchess' center-parted hair and floral dress to American socialite who led Harry's great-uncle King Edward VIII to abdicate
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/femail/article-9318273/Did-Meghan-Markle-style-inspiration-Wallis-Simpson-Oprah-interview.html">
           <img alt="Did Meghan Markle take style inspiration from Wallis Simpson for her Oprah interview?" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/23/39966484-0-image-a-44_1614728730890.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="Did Meghan Markle take style inspiration from Wallis Simpson for her Oprah interview?" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/23/39966484-0-image-a-44_1614728730890.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            In the teasers for Meghan and Harry: A CBS Primetime Special, the pregnant Duchess of Sussex can be seen wearing a $4,700 black floral dress by Armani. Viewers were quick to point out that the 39-year-old's outfit and center-parted hairstyle were incredibly similar to a look worn by Wallis in an early portrait. The photograph was taken before she was the Duchess of Windsor in 1936, the same year King Edward VIII abdicated the throne to marry her. Meghan, who has been wearing her hair in loose waves in California, appeared to be sporting a modern version of Simpson's pulled-back finger waves. She also paired a Cartier diamond tennis bracelet from Princess Diana's jewelry collection with her Cartier Love Bracelet. The Windsors both had earlier versions of the Cartier Love Bracelet. Meghan and Wallishave regularly been compared to each other as the American divorcees both married British royals who stepped down from their royal duties.
           </p>
          </div>

        <div class="article article-tri-headline exclusive" itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem">
         <meta content="40" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9313587/Meghan-Markle-planning-bombshell-interview-Oprah-two-YEARS.html" itemprop="url">
           Meghan Markle has been planning tell-all interview with Oprah for two years - since the palace's PR team squashed the Sussexes' sit down with Gayle King in 2019
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/news/article-9313587/Meghan-Markle-planning-bombshell-interview-Oprah-two-YEARS.html">
           <img alt="Meghan Markle has been planning bombshell interview with Oprah for two YEARS" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/01/21/39919978-0-image-a-86_1614633619513.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="Meghan Markle has been planning bombshell interview with Oprah for two YEARS" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/01/21/39919978-0-image-a-86_1614633619513.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            Meghan originally tried to arrange a televised talk with friend and CBS anchor Gayle King after her son Archie's birth in May 2019. But the Duchess of Sussex was overruled by the Royal Family's public relations machine, sources tell DailyMail.com. Insiders say King and Oprah have been in talks over a sit-down with the Sussexes ever since, eventually leading to the interview set to air on CBS on March 7. Meghan was hoping to do a 'short interview' in 2019 about her time adjusting to Royal life and becoming a mother. PR at Kensington Palace quickly put a stop to the plans fearing 'it would alienate the UK press', a source close to the controversy said. 'They were emphatically told she could not conduct her own lengthy interviews with US media friends after Archie's birth,' the source said. The source said there was 'an element of feeling handcuffed' and 'not having full ownership of their image'.
           </p>
          </div>

        <div class="article article-tri-headline" itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem">
         <meta content="43" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9318059/Michigan-professor-says-hes-discriminated-against-40-years-white-man.html" itemprop="url">
           Michigan professor says he's been 'systematically discriminated against for 40 years for being a white man' and demands apology from university over its new anti-racism policies
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/news/article-9318059/Michigan-professor-says-hes-discriminated-against-40-years-white-man.html">
           <img alt="Michigan professor says he's been 'discriminated against for 40 years for being a white" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/20/39961018-0-image-a-15_1614716566017.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="Michigan professor says he's been 'discriminated against for 40 years for being a white" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/20/39961018-0-image-a-15_1614716566017.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            Jeffrey Burl, left, wrote to his employers, right, Michigan Technological University, inset, after they passed a resolution criticizing 'anti-Blackness and systemic racism'. In his letter Burl, who is an associate professor of electrical and computer engineering, writes: 'I find this resolution particularly offensive.' 'I have been systematically discriminated against for 40 years', he adds. His message has sparked outrage among some students, with Michigan Tech alumni Timothy Ward creating a petition to demanding he be fired. Burl goes on in his letter, sent in January: 'At Michigan Tech, I have seen no signs (in my 28 years here) of discrimination against women and people of color'.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>

        <div class="article article-tri-headline">
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/sciencetech/article-9318267/Deepfake-Tom-Cruise-takes-TikTok-11-million-views-raises-alarms-experts.html">
           'Deepfake' Tom Cruise takes over TikTok: Three videos with more than 11 million views spark fears among experts who say they are 'the most alarming lifelike examples'
          </a>
         </h2>
         <a href="/sciencetech/article-9318267/Deepfake-Tom-Cruise-takes-TikTok-11-million-views-raises-alarms-experts.html">
          <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/1765184036532368802/308x174_JPG_1765184036532368802.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="70" data-frame-height="172" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/1765184036532368802/636x382_JPG-HD_1765184036532368802.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="70" data-hd-frame-height="356" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/1765184036532368802/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_1765184036532368802.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/1765184036532368802/636x382_MP4_1765184036532368802.mp4" height="356" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="636"/>
          <noscript>
           <img height="356" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/1765184036532368802/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_1765184036532368802.jpg" width="636"/>
          </noscript>
         </a>
         <div class="articletext">
          <div>
           <p>
            Videos showing who appears to be Tom Cruise on TikTok are actually deepfakes of the celebrity. Three videos have been posted, which have more than 11 million views together. However, the clips are raising concerns among experts who fear these lifelike examples could pave the way for the technology to manipulate the public.
           </p>

         <div class="gradient-split wocc link-wocc linkro-wocc">
          <h6>
           BIDEN ADMINISTRATION
          </h6>
          <div>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="article article-tri-headline" itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem">
         <meta content="49" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9317847/Detailed-composition-MAGA-riot-emerges-250-arrests.html" itemprop="url">
           Breakdown of 250 arrested MAGA rioters show there were seven Proud Boys, four Oath Keepers with military ties, 36 women and the highest number came from LA County
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/news/article-9317847/Detailed-composition-MAGA-riot-emerges-250-arrests.html">
           <img alt="Detailed composition of MAGA riot emerges in more than 250 arrests" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/20/39962408-0-image-a-9_1614716829699.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="Detailed composition of MAGA riot emerges in more than 250 arrests" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/20/39962408-0-image-a-9_1614716829699.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            A new analysis of 257 finds 221 men and 36 women charged in the riots - with 33 members identified as having military backgrounds. Among that group, a dozen were tied to extremist groups like the Oath Keepers and Proud Boys. Charges range from trespassing to conspiracy against the U.S. government, with people from 40 states and Washington, D.C. charged so far.
           </p>
          </div>

         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/femail/article-9317811/THREE-YEAR-OLD-chef-earns-TikTok-fame-cooking-skills.html">
           Look out Gordon Ramsay! Three-year-old chef wows TikTok with his amazing cooking skills - as videos show him chopping and frying ingredients while whipping up dishes like beef Wellington, roast chicken and pizza
          </a>
         </h2>
         <a href="/femail/article-9317811/THREE-YEAR-OLD-chef-earns-TikTok-fame-cooking-skills.html">
          <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4265627167448218572/308x174_JPG_4265627167448218572.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="65" data-frame-height="172" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4265627167448218572/636x382_JPG-HD_4265627167448218572.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="66" data-hd-frame-height="356" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4265627167448218572/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_4265627167448218572.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4265627167448218572/636x382_MP4_4265627167448218572.mp4" height="356" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="636"/>
          <noscript>
           <img height="356" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4265627167448218572/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_4265627167448218572.jpg" width="636"/>
          </noscript>
         </a>
         <div class="articletext">
          <div>
           <p>
            Chef Ilirian Kameraj from Great Neck, New York, has been experimenting in the kitchen with his mom since he was less than a year old. He wanted to learn to bake after seeing a character do it on a kids' YouTube show he likes. During the pandemic, his mother,Dorentina, started filming his cooking experiments and sharing them on YouTube. The little boy wears a chef's hat and mixes ingredients, tenderized meat, and even chops vegetables with a safe chopping machine. He has made spaghetti and meatballs, pizza, rack of lamb, pumpkin pie, egg frittata, skirt steak and potatoes, turkey, burgers, cakes, cookies, and more.
           </p>
          </div>

         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/femail/article-9316983/HIlaria-Baldwin-confirms-welcomed-daughter-named-Lucia.html" itemprop="url">
           Alec Baldwin tells trolls to 'shut the f*** up' after being asked to identify the mother of newborn daughter Lucia - who was born just six months after Hilaria gave birth to couple's fifth child
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/femail/article-9316983/HIlaria-Baldwin-confirms-welcomed-daughter-named-Lucia.html">
           <img alt="HIlaria Baldwin welcomes baby girl with six months after birth of her son" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/18/39958144-0-image-m-2_1614709065476.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="HIlaria Baldwin welcomes baby girl with six months after birth of her son" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/18/39958144-0-image-m-2_1614709065476.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            The Boston-born mother-of-six took to Instagram on Tuesday morning to confirm the gender and name of the couple's newborn daughter while sharing a photo of the baby girl (right). Hilaria, 37, revealed that they have given the baby girl a Spanish name - just like their five other children. Lucia's arrival sparked many questions when Hilaria shared the news on Monday, and the couple have yet to share whether she was adopted or born via surrogate. The baby girl arrived just six months after Hilaria gave birth to her son, Edu, who was born after the yoga guru suffered two miscarriages. On Monday, Alec took to Instagram to slam commenters who questioned him about Lucia's arrival, dropping the F-bomb in one particularly furious rant. Hilaria's reveal of her daughter's name - which means 'light' in Spanish - comes just weeks after the wellness expert was accused of faking her Spanish heritage.
           </p>

            </a>
           </h2>
           <div class="articletext">
            <a href="/news/article-9317507/Judge-says-one-member-George-Floyds-family-allowed-Derek-Chauvin-trial.html">
             <img alt="" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/17/39956710-0-image-a-4_1614706471118.jpg" height="115" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="154"/>

             </noscript>
            </a>
            <p>
             The judge overseeing the trial of ex-Minneapolis cop Derek Chauvin (right), who faces murder and manslaughter charges in the death of George Floyd (left), made announcement on Tuesday.
            </p>

        <div class="article article-tri-headline">
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9318057/Eddie-Murphy-Arsenio-Hall-forced-cast-Louie-Anderson-Coming-America.html">
           'We were forced to put in a white person': Eddie Murphy and Arsenio Hall reveal Paramount Pictures 'made them cast Louie Anderson in the original Coming to America'
          </a>
         </h2>
         <a href="/news/article-9318057/Eddie-Murphy-Arsenio-Hall-forced-cast-Louie-Anderson-Coming-America.html">
          <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7279936781507841888/308x174_JPG_7279936781507841888.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="68" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7279936781507841888/636x382_JPG-HD_7279936781507841888.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="67" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7279936781507841888/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_7279936781507841888.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7279936781507841888/636x382_MP4_7279936781507841888.mp4" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="636"/>
          <noscript>
           <img height="382" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7279936781507841888/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_7279936781507841888.jpg" width="636"/>
          </noscript>
         </a>
         <div class="articletext">
          <div>
           <p>
            Eddie Murphy and Arsenio Hall (seen second from right and far right, respectively) have claimed that Paramount Pictures forced them to cast a white man in their 1988 hit comedy film Coming to America. The stars of the upcoming sequel, which is titled Coming 2 America, revealed that the edict from the studio is what led comedian Louie Anderson (seen inset with Murphy in the original 1988 film) to be cast in the role of Maurice. 'I love Louie, but I think we were forced to put Louie in it,' Hall told Jimmy Kimmel Live (left) as he appeared remotely alongside Murphy to promote the highly anticipated sequel, which will be released digitally by Amazon on Friday. 'We were forced to put in a white person.' Murphy told Kimmel that Paramount was adamant that the cast of the film, which included James Earl Jones, Shari Headley, John Amos, and Samuel L. Jackson, not be comprised exclusively of African Americans. The actor appeared to imply that given it was the late 1980s, the studio felt the film would be more marketable to white audiences if there was a white actor cast in one of the supporting roles. 'They were like, "There has to be a white person in the movie",' Murphy, who plays the lead role, King Akeem, in the sequel, as well as a host of other characters in disguise. 'I was like, "What?" Murphy added: 'So who was the funniest white guy around? We knew Louie was cool, so that's how Louie got in the movie.'
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>
         <div class="article-icon-links-container" data-followbutton="MailOnline" data-social-first-article-links="">

             <span class="linktext">
              <span class="bold">

         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9317369/Five-armed-teens-aged-14-17-arrested-hotel-robbery.html">
           Dramatic video shows cops in gun fight with five teens, aged 14 to 17, armed with an arsenal of guns including an AR-15 who 'burst into a hotel room, robbed a guest and fled in a BMW'
          </a>
         </h2>
         <a href="/news/article-9317369/Five-armed-teens-aged-14-17-arrested-hotel-robbery.html">
          <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7205869907742969066/308x174_JPG_7205869907742969066.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="61" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7205869907742969066/636x382_JPG-HD_7205869907742969066.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="60" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7205869907742969066/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_7205869907742969066.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7205869907742969066/636x382_MP4_7205869907742969066.mp4" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="636"/>
          <noscript>
           <img height="382" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7205869907742969066/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_7205869907742969066.jpg" width="636"/>
          </noscript>
         </a>
         <div class="articletext">
          <div>
           <p>
            Police in California have released details concerning an armed hotel robbery and officer-involved shooting that led to the arrests of four teenage boys and a girl, ages 14 to 17. The juvenile suspects are suspected of barging into a hotel room, stealing a guest's car keys and phone, and then leading police on a chase in a stolen BMW.
           </p>

            </a>

           <div class="articletext">

        <div class="article article-tri-headline exclusive" itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem">
         <meta content="70" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9286971/How-Pan-stewardesses-playgirls-air.html" itemprop="url">
           Seducing passengers, skinny-dipping with expats, and partying in between flights: How Pan Am stewardesses became the 'playgirls of the air' during the Golden Age of Travel
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/news/article-9286971/How-Pan-stewardesses-playgirls-air.html">
           <img alt="How Pan Am stewardesses became the 'playgirls of the air'" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/02/23/19/39680170-0-image-a-50_1614109395947.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="How Pan Am stewardesses became the 'playgirls of the air'" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/02/23/19/39680170-0-image-a-50_1614109395947.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            In addition to being pioneers of the modern air travel industry, Pan American Airways became famous for its flight attendants, back then referred to as stewardesses, who were trained to provide top-notch service on board. The world famous airline offered young, unmarried - and mostly white - women a chance to become globetrotters with a position that allowed them to explore foreign cultures, nightlife in exotic cities, and sexual encounters overseas. It was an enticing offer for sophisticated young women yearning for something more than graduate school, staid jobs after college where career options were limited or marriage and a family. The jetsetting lives of these women are documented by Julia Cooke, the daughter of a former Pan Am executive, in Come Fly the World: the Jet-Age Story of the Women of Pan-Am, published on March 2.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>
         <div class="article-icon-links-container" data-followbutton="MailOnline">
          <ul class="article-icon-links cleared">
           <li class="first">

        <div class="article article-tri-headline" itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem">
         <meta content="73" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/femail/article-9313413/London-estate-agent-enlisted-help-sell-Americas-expensive-house.html" itemprop="url">
           A slice of Hollywood history for sale! New real estate agent is brought in to market William Randolph Hearst's $119M Beverly Hills mansion which featured in The Godfather, The Bodyguard and Beyonc's Black Is King after a decade without a buyer
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/femail/article-9313413/London-estate-agent-enlisted-help-sell-Americas-expensive-house.html">
           <img alt="London estate agent is enlisted to help sell America'smost expensive house" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/21/39963414-0-image-m-10_1614721671855.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="London estate agent is enlisted to help sell America'smost expensive house" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/21/39963414-0-image-m-10_1614721671855.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            It's a Beverly Hills mansion with a rich Hollywood history, yet Beverly House, an 18-bedroom, 25-bathroom property set on 3.5 acres, has been on and off the market for more than a decade without a buyer. It was listed in 2007 for $165million, in 2010 for $95million, in 2016 for $195million, and most recently for $119million - with its present price making it the most expensive house on the market in America. But with no buyer coming forward, its US agents, The Agency, have enlisted the help of London-based Beauchamp Estates, known for its super-rich clientele, to assist securing a deal for the former private palace (pictured left inset) and estate of newspaper tycoon William Randolph Hearst. Built in 1927, the house is heralded as a symbol of Hollywood's Golden Age, and famed for its well-known scenes inThe Godfather starring Marlon Brando in 1972, in The Bodyguard featuring Whitney Houston and Kevin Costner in 1992 and inBeyonc's visual album Black Is King (pictured right inset). Pictured clockwise from top left: The lavish living space, the Art Deco-style nightclub, the glamorous gardens and the Olympic-size swimming pool.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>

           <meta content="74" itemprop="position"/>
           <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
            <a href="/sciencetech/article-9317237/Belly-fat-resistant-weight-loss.html" itemprop="url">
             Is THIS why it's so difficult to get a six pack? Belly fat is the most resistant to weight loss - even when fasting every other day, scientists reveal
            </a>
           </h2>
           <div class="articletext">
            <a href="/sciencetech/article-9317237/Belly-fat-resistant-weight-loss.html">
             <img alt="" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/15/39951780-0-image-m-7_1614700385697.jpg" height="115" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="154"/>
             <noscript>
              <img alt="" height="115" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/15/39951780-0-image-m-7_1614700385697.jpg" width="154"/>
             </noscript>
            </a>
            <p>
             Scientists discovered belly fat is difficult to shift during intermittent fasting due to a 'preservation mode' which allows it to stay put while fat around the rest of the body is shifted.
            </p>
           </div>
           <div class="article-icon-links-container" data-followbutton="MailOnline">

           Why didn't I think of that? Social media snaps reveal VERY simple solutions to everyday problems - from an end to pesky food stickers to elevator buttons you can press with your feet
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/femail/article-9313661/People-share-ingenious-designs-make-everyday-tasks-easier.html">
           <img alt="People share ingenious designs that make everyday tasks much easier" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/08/39937682-0-image-a-7_1614672191954.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>

           <p>
            These easy yet effective solutions to everyday problems prove that sometimes the simplest ideas are the best. Snaps of the brilliant designs were taken in the UK and US, with the best examples collated in a gallery by Bored Panda. Pictured clockwise from top left: a solution for produce stickers; a magnifying glass to read the small print; a mini toilet roll inside the toilet roll; two types of soap for before and after dinner; foot buttons to save your fingers; an alarm checker/

          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/femail/article-9317873/Paulina-Porizkova-regrets-giving-late-husband-Ric-Ocasek-control-money.html">
           <img alt="Paulina Porizkova regrets giving late husband Ric Ocasek control of her money" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/19/39961192-0-image-a-101_1614714971019.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="Paulina Porizkova regrets giving late husband Ric Ocasek control of her money" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/19/39961192-0-image-a-101_1614714971019.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            Paulina, 55, took to Instagram on Tuesday to share a photo collage featuring dozens of magazines that she had covered throughout her career. In the post, which was part of her partnership with UBS bank, she recalled how she didn't have 'any sense of financial worth' at the height of her success. Even though she starred on hundreds of covers and had lucrative contracts, she let her financial managers control her money. Paulina, who didn't have a prenup, said she let Ric control her money when they got married, which essentially meant he was controlling her. The model said people in the fashion industry would 'lose respect' for her and think she was the 'vapid wife of a rockstar' when they found out. Ric cut Paulina out of his will after they separated and left her without any money to live off of when he died in September 2019 at age 75.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>

            </a>
           </h2>
           <div class="articletext">
            <a href="/health/article-9316943/Merck-help-Johnson-Johnson-produce-one-dose-COVID-19-vaccine-historic-partnership.html">
             <img alt="" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/19/39950760-0-image-a-44_1614711895277.jpg" height="115" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="154"/>

             </noscript>
            </a>

             President Joe Biden will announce on Tuesday that Merck &amp; Co will help produce Johnson &amp; Johnson's one-shot coronavirus vaccine, dedicating two facilities to the task.

         <div class="thin-split ccox link-ccox linkro-box bdrcc">
          <h6>
          </h6>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="article article-tri-headline">
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9318261/Five-Bolivian-students-die-three-injured-fourth-storey-railing-collapses-stairwell.html">
           At least five students die and three are injured after railing collapsed and sent people plummeting from fourth-floor balcony outside a Bolivian university protest meeting
          </a>
         </h2>
         <a href="/news/article-9318261/Five-Bolivian-students-die-three-injured-fourth-storey-railing-collapses-stairwell.html">
          <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/790087839551407450/308x174_JPG_790087839551407450.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="34" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/790087839551407450/636x382_JPG-HD_790087839551407450.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="34" data-hd-frame-height="380" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/790087839551407450/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_790087839551407450.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/790087839551407450/636x382_MP4_790087839551407450.mp4" height="380" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="636"/>
          <noscript>
           <img height="380" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/790087839551407450/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_790087839551407450.jpg" width="636"/>
          </noscript>
         </a>
         <div class="articletext">
          <div>
           <p>
            WARNING GRAPHIC CONTENT: A large group of youngsters at the University of El Alto were crowding outside a protest meeting when the metal barrier snapped. Horrifying footage shows the moment the thronging crowd trying to enter the student assembly on Tuesday. Two women and one man were killed by the fall, while five other men were taken to hospital after the fall. Two of them have since died as a result of their injuries.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>

        <div class="article article-tri-headline" itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem">
         <meta content="98" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9317443/Facebook-new-data-center-takes-shape-Utah.html" itemprop="url">
           New pictures show Facebook's massive new data center in Utah: Tech giant announces they will add a further900,000 square feet to house servers
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/news/article-9317443/Facebook-new-data-center-takes-shape-Utah.html">
           <img alt="Facebook new data center takes shape in Utah" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/16/39955076-0-image-a-55_1614704137649.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="Facebook new data center takes shape in Utah" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/16/39955076-0-image-a-55_1614704137649.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            The Eagle Mountain Data Center will house some of Facebook's vast network of servers, joining other sites belonging to the tech giant in the United States, Denmark, Sweden, Ireland and Singapore. Construction began in 2018, with 12,000 tons of steel and 100,000 cubic yards of concrete being hauled into place to put together three buildings which Facebook says will eventually be solar-powered.And even though construction is not yet complete, Facebook announced last month that two more buildings will be added to the Eagle Mountain complex, expanding the site by a further 900,000 square feet.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>

           <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
            <a href="/news/article-9316633/Denmark-European-country-Syrian-migrants-country.html" itemprop="url">
             Denmark becomes the first European nation to tell Syrian refugees they must return home, saying the country is now safe
            </a>
           </h2>
           <div class="articletext">
            <a href="/news/article-9316633/Denmark-European-country-Syrian-migrants-country.html">
             <img alt="" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/13/39947334-0-image-m-14_1614691786168.jpg" height="115" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="154"/>

        <div class="article article-tri-headline" itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem">
         <meta content="101" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9317041/Photos-elite-Allied-soldiers-storming-Italian-airbase-Libya-1942-Operation-Caravan.html" itemprop="url">
           The ultimate WRECKING crew! Unseen photos show elite Allied soldiers storming Italian airbase in Libya during 1942 Operation Caravan that destroyed 23 warplanes... and caused a total headache for Hitler
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/news/article-9317041/Photos-elite-Allied-soldiers-storming-Italian-airbase-Libya-1942-Operation-Caravan.html">
           <img alt="Photos show elite Allied soldiers storming Italian airbase in Libya during 1942 Operation" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/15/39953078-0-image-a-103_1614700244251.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="Photos show elite Allied soldiers storming Italian airbase in Libya during 1942 Operation" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/15/39953078-0-image-a-103_1614700244251.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            Operation Caravan - carried out in September 1942 - saw members of the elite Long Range Desert Group (LRDG) attack the town of Barce and its accompanying airbase, in northern Libya. The men stormed into the base and town in the dead of night with orders to 'cause the maximum amount of damage and disturbance to the enemy.' They destroyed or damaged 23 Italian planes which were being used to drop bombs on Allied troops. The men also destroyed transport, fuel and ammo supplies - severely hampering the Italian operation in North Africa, which Adolf Hitler's Nazis relied upon to keep Britain and its allies at bay in the region. The previously unpublished pictured are revealed in book The Long Range Desert Group in Action 1940-1943, written by military historian Brendan O'Carroll. Pictured clockwise from top left: Trooper R.E. Hay behind his .303 Vickers heavy machine gun before the raid; Corporal M.H. Craw of the LRDG's T1 Patrol. He stands draped in machine-gun belts before the raid, for which he won the Military Medal; The underside view of the LRDG truck which failed to make it out of Barce after it crashed; members of the LRDG are given a talk by Captain N.P. Wilder on the day before the attack. Inset: The jeep which crashed before the mission, injuring Captain Timpson and Guardsman Wilder.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>
         <div class="article-icon-links-container" data-followbutton="MailOnline">
          <ul class="article-icon-links cleared">
           <li class="first">

             <span class="icon">
             </span>

         <meta content="104" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9316891/Woman-69-gave-birth-twins-aged-64-ruled-unfit-care-Spanish-court.html" itemprop="url">
           Mother, 69, who gave birth to twins aged 64 following IVF has her children taken into custody after Spanish court rules she cannot care for them
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/news/article-9316891/Woman-69-gave-birth-twins-aged-64-ruled-unfit-care-Spanish-court.html">
           <img alt="Woman, 69, who gave birth to twins aged 64 is ruled unfit to care for them by Spanish" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/14/39950318-0-image-a-2_1614696536334.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="Woman, 69, who gave birth to twins aged 64 is ruled unfit to care for them by Spanish" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/14/39950318-0-image-a-2_1614696536334.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            A 69-year-old woman (pictured) has lost custody of the twins she gave birth to aged 64 after Spain's highest court ruled that she was incapable of looking after them. The Spanish Supreme Court upheld an April 22, 2020 ruling to remove the children, handed down by the Provincial Court of Burgos, which found that the twins were not being cared for in 'optimal conditions'. The Supreme Court ruling brings to an end a four-year legal battle by the woman, Mauricia Ibanez, who gave birth to the twins in 2017 after having fertility treatment in the United States. The court found that the twins were 'in an obvious situation of vulnerability' due to their mother's inability to care for them properly or to cooperate with social services. The decision was not based on the woman's age or mental health, the court said, but rather on the 'evaluations of experts.'
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>

           <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
            <a href="/sciencetech/article-9317727/NASAs-Perseverance-rover-running-processor-used-iconic-1998-Apple-iMac-G3.html" itemprop="url">
             NASA's Perseverance rover is running on the same processor used in the iconic, colorful 1998 Apple iMac G3 while it treks around Mars in search of life
            </a>
           </h2>
           <div class="articletext">
            <a href="/sciencetech/article-9317727/NASAs-Perseverance-rover-running-processor-used-iconic-1998-Apple-iMac-G3.html">
             <img alt="" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/17/39957028-0-image-a-29_1614707083494.jpg" height="115" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="154"/>
             <noscript>
              <img alt="" height="115" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/17/39957028-0-image-a-29_1614707083494.jpg" width="154"/>
             </noscript>
            </a>
            <p>
             NASA's Perseverance is fitted with advanced cameras, radars and even a laser, but the car-sized rover is running on the same processor Apple used in its iconic iMac G3 released in 1998.
            </p>
           </div>
           <div class="article-icon-links-container" data-followbutton="MailOnline">

         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/femail/article-9316991/Glee-cast-members-rough-filming-experience-admitting-stars-hated-show.html">
           Former Glee stars detail their 'rough' filming experiences, admit some cast members 'HATED' the show and slam 'tone deaf' cultural story lines in resurfaced video
          </a>
         </h2>
         <a href="/femail/article-9316991/Glee-cast-members-rough-filming-experience-admitting-stars-hated-show.html">
          <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/5488124278755931664/308x174_JPG_5488124278755931664.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="57" data-frame-height="172" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/5488124278755931664/636x382_JPG-HD_5488124278755931664.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="58" data-hd-frame-height="356" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/5488124278755931664/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_5488124278755931664.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/5488124278755931664/636x382_MP4_5488124278755931664.mp4" height="356" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="636"/>
          <noscript>
           <img height="356" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/5488124278755931664/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_5488124278755931664.jpg" width="636"/>
          </noscript>
         </a>
         <div class="articletext">
          <div>
           <p>
            Jenna Ushkowitz, 34, and Kevin McHale, 32, played Tina and Artie on the popular musical show from 2009 to 2015. A 2020 podcast interview with the stars is going viral on TikTok. Kevin says he never 'hated' the show but 'some people did'; he admitted that he 'broke' when he had to sing 'What Does the Fox Say.' Jenna said that season five 'was really rough for us' and agreed that the show was 'tone deaf' - like when she had to sing Psy's Gangnam Style. They also discussed how 'creepy' Matthew Morrison's character Mr. Schue was.
           </p>

             Boy Scouts of America offers $300million and its collection of Norman Rockwell paintings to settle more than 95,000 sexual abuse claims
            </a>
           </h2>
           <div class="articletext">
            <a href="/news/article-9315205/Boy-Scouts-submit-reorganization-plan-bankruptcy-court.html">
             <img alt="" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/16/39953340-0-image-a-9_1614701333989.jpg" height="115" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="154"/>
             <noscript>
              <img alt="" height="115" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/16/39953340-0-image-a-9_1614701333989.jpg" width="154"/>
             </noscript>
            </a>
            <p>
             The Boy Scouts of America is offering $220million as well as its collection of Norman Rockwell paintings in order to settle more than 95,000 lawsuits filed by alleged sexual abuse victims.

         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/sciencetech/article-9316501/400-000-foldable-MicroLED-TV-disappears-floor.html">
           World's first FOLDABLE TV unveiled with 165-inch screen that disappears into your floor - but it has an eye-watering $400,000 price tag
          </a>
         </h2>
         <a href="/sciencetech/article-9316501/400-000-foldable-MicroLED-TV-disappears-floor.html">
          <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/3834544390552140823/308x174_JPG_3834544390552140823.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="70" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/3834544390552140823/636x382_JPG-HD_3834544390552140823.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="70" data-hd-frame-height="380" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/3834544390552140823/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_3834544390552140823.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/3834544390552140823/636x382_MP4_3834544390552140823.mp4" height="380" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="636"/>
          <noscript>
           <img height="380" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/3834544390552140823/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_3834544390552140823.jpg" width="636"/>
          </noscript>
         </a>
         <div class="articletext">
          <div>
           <p>
            A consumer tech company has unveiled a MicroLED TV made up of five panels that rise up from the floor, unfold and click into place to form one huge display. The luxury object,called M1, is the creation of C SEED Entertainment, which has offices in Vienna, Austria and California. M1 retails for $400,000 (around 290,000) but its hefty price tag doesn't include installation, which would require enough space to hide it underground.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>

          </a>
         </h2>
         <a href="/news/article-9316291/7ft-9in-Nigerian-hopes-NBAs-tallest-player-Shaq-shared-viral-footage-him.html">
          <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7846013527639739286/308x174_JPG_7846013527639739286.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="36" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7846013527639739286/636x382_JPG-HD_7846013527639739286.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="36" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7846013527639739286/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_7846013527639739286.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7846013527639739286/636x382_MP4_7846013527639739286.mp4" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="636"/>
          <noscript>
           <img height="382" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/7846013527639739286/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_7846013527639739286.jpg" width="636"/>
          </noscript>
         </a>
         <div class="articletext">
          <div>
           <p>
            A 7ft 9in Nigerian basketball player is hoping to catch the attention of the NBA after Shaquille O'Neal shared viral footage of him on the court. At his towering height, Abiodun Adegoke can dunk with both feet still on the ground, and if signed, would become the league's tallest ever player. The viral video shows the centre, 18, dunking the ball with ease at a youth development camp in Dubai. Despite his height, Adegoke moves with agility, making short work of the diminutive defence. The clip was shared by legendary four-time NBA champion O'Neal, who also played centre. Adegoke is currently training with the MPAC Sports UAE system as he makes plans for his future. He has so far been overlooked by American scouts, perhaps due to controversy surrounding his age, the Daily Star reported. Nigerian media reports from 2016 gave the player's age as 17. At the time he was a student of a sports academy in Lagos. Adegoke insists he is 18.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>
