          <h6>
          </h6>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="article article-tri-headline" itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope="" itemtype="//schema.org/ListItem">
         <meta content="129" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/sciencetech/article-9317071/The-Great-Pacific-Garbage-Patch-connecting-pathway-Asia-feeding-debris.html" itemprop="url">
           Unraveling the mystery of the 'Great Pacific Garbage Patch': Floating landfill twice the size of TEXAS in the North Pacific may get most of its plastic debris from eastern Asia, study reveals
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/sciencetech/article-9317071/The-Great-Pacific-Garbage-Patch-connecting-pathway-Asia-feeding-debris.html">
           <img alt="Great Pacific Garbage Patch has 'connecting pathway with East Asia' that may feed it" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/16/39954504-0-image-a-14_1614702789886.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="Great Pacific Garbage Patch has 'connecting pathway with East Asia' that may feed it" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/16/39954504-0-image-a-14_1614702789886.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            US and German scientists may have solved what is feeding the Great Pacific Garbage Patch, which is a plastic landfill twice the size of Texas. The team found the majority of the trash is flowing from a transition channel that connects the garbage patch with eastern Asia (inset). Researchers used a Marvok model (main) to determine probabilities of pathways that are transporting debris to the Great Pacific Garbage Patch. The model also identified he weakness of the circulating system in the Indian Ocean is also a trap for plastics andthe North Pacific subtropical gyre attracts the most debris.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>

           <meta content="131" itemprop="position"/>
           <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
            <a href="/femail/article-9315939/Amputee-lost-limbs-toxic-reaction.html" itemprop="url">
             Quadruple amputee who claims her husband left her while she fought for her life after a toxic reaction to medication claims her life is BETTER now because she's 'living with purpose'
            </a>
           </h2>
           <div class="articletext">
            <a href="/femail/article-9315939/Amputee-lost-limbs-toxic-reaction.html">
             <img alt="" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/09/39940102-0-image-a-19_1614677233807.jpg" height="115" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="154"/>
             <noscript>
              <img alt="" height="115" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/09/39940102-0-image-a-19_1614677233807.jpg" width="154"/>
             </noscript>
            </a>
            <p>
             WARNING: GRAPHIC CONTENT Kim Gilliam Steele, 54, from Georgia, says she decided to turn her life around after the traumatic operation and says she tries to always spread positivity.
            </p>
           </div>

            </a>
           </h2>
           <div class="articletext">
            <a href="/news/article-9315327/Houston-man-30-shot-dead-trying-stolen-car-running-car-thief.html">
             <img alt="" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/06/39935014-0-image-a-15_1614665989842.jpg" height="115" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="154"/>

           <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
            <a href="/sciencetech/article-9315751/Painstaking-study-Little-Foot-fossil-sheds-light-human-origins.html" itemprop="url">
             X-ray of our ancient ancestor Little Foot's skull suggests she was 'relatively old' when she died 3.67 million years ago and survived two childhood bouts of physiological stress such as disease or malnutrition
            </a>
           </h2>
           <div class="articletext">
            <a href="/sciencetech/article-9315751/Painstaking-study-Little-Foot-fossil-sheds-light-human-origins.html">
             <img alt="" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/10/39942054-0-image-m-16_1614680942868.jpg" height="115" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="154"/>
             <noscript>
              <img alt="" height="115" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/10/39942054-0-image-m-16_1614680942868.jpg" width="154"/>
             </noscript>
            </a>
            <p>
             Discovered in South Africa in the mid-90s Little Foot's fossil was analysed in Oxfordshire with super high resolution X-ray images.
            </p>
           </div>
           <div class="article-icon-links-container" data-followbutton="MailOnline">
            <ul class="article-icon-links cleared">
             <li class="first">

        <div class="article article-tri-headline">
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9315857/Fidel-Castros-grandson-sparks-fury-video-boasting-speeding-luxury-car-Cuba.html">
           Fidel Castro's nightclub-owning grandson sparks fury with video boasting about speeding in his luxury Mercedes in Cuba as the country suffers COVID economic crisis
          </a>
         </h2>
         <a href="/news/article-9315857/Fidel-Castros-grandson-sparks-fury-video-boasting-speeding-luxury-car-Cuba.html">
          <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/1760831284596554878/308x174_JPG_1760831284596554878.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="64" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/1760831284596554878/636x382_JPG-HD_1760831284596554878.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="65" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/1760831284596554878/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_1760831284596554878.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/1760831284596554878/636x382_MP4_1760831284596554878.mp4" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="636"/>
          <noscript>
           <img height="382" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/1760831284596554878/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_1760831284596554878.jpg" width="636"/>
          </noscript>
         </a>
         <div class="articletext">
          <div>
           <p>
            Sandro Castro (pictured left and right), a nightclub owner, was seen in a video speeding along a deserted Cuban motorway as the country faces its worst economic crisis since the 1990s amidst the coronavirus pandemic. In Cuba, there is a 100 km/h speed limit (62 mph) on motorways due to poor road conditions, but Fidel Castro's (pictured top-inset) grandson is shown doing almost 90 mph. Sandro Castro - who is said to be in his early twenties - faced criticism for posting the video from some traditional supporters of the revolution, who accused him of gross hypocrisy. Sandro Castro reportedly has a reputation as being the most ostentatious of the former communist dictator's grandchildren.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>

         <meta content="135" itemprop="position"/>
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/femail/article-9316623/Prince-Oscar-Sweden-poses-Cavapoo-puppy-adorable-new-fifth-birthday-portraits.html" itemprop="url">
           Birthday boy! Prince Oscar of Sweden poses with his Cavapoo puppy in adorable new portraits released to celebrate royal turning five
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/femail/article-9316623/Prince-Oscar-Sweden-poses-Cavapoo-puppy-adorable-new-fifth-birthday-portraits.html">
           <img alt="Prince Oscar of Sweden poses with hisCavapoo puppy in adorable new fifth birthday" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/13/39947644-0-image-a-36_1614691576743.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="Prince Oscar of Sweden poses with hisCavapoo puppy in adorable new fifth birthday" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/13/39947644-0-image-a-36_1614691576743.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            Prince Oscar of Sweden (pictured) has delighted royal fans after appearing in new portraits released to celebrate his fifth birthday. The youngest child of Sweden's heir apparent Crown Princess Victoria and Prince Daniel beamed in the photographs, showcasing him alongside his petCavapoo puppyat Haga Palace, in Stockholm. In a final snap, the prince is joined by his older sisterPrincess Estelle (pictured right), nine,who is second in line to the Swedish throne, as the siblings play in a snow-covered field.
           </p>
          </div>

         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9314311/Photo-yellow-faced-whip-snake-hiding-bushland-leaves-Australians-baffled.html" itemprop="url">
           Hide and ssss-eek! Can you spot the snake hiding in Australian bushland?
          </a>
         </h2>
         <div class="articletext">
          <a href="/news/article-9314311/Photo-yellow-faced-whip-snake-hiding-bushland-leaves-Australians-baffled.html">
           <img alt="Photo of a yellow-faced whip snake hiding in bushland leaves Australians baffled" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/00/39922894-0-image-a-3_1614646047849.jpg" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="max-width:100%" width="636"/>
           <noscript>
            <img alt="Photo of a yellow-faced whip snake hiding in bushland leaves Australians baffled" height="382" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2021/03/02/00/39922894-0-image-a-3_1614646047849.jpg" width="636"/>
           </noscript>
          </a>
          <div>
           <p>
            A picture of a snake camouflaged in the bush after being released has left people stumped. The photo was taken on the Sunshine Coast in Little Mountain, Queensland shortly after the captured yellow-faced whip snake was set free. Sunshine Coast Snake Catchers then shared the image as part of their weekly 'spot the snake' series.
           </p>

       <div class="alpha">
        <div class="article article-tri-headline">
         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9315971/Russian-snowmobile-riders-chase-pregnant-elk-jump-animal-STRANGLE-it.html">
           Russian snowmobile riders chase down pregnant elk until it collapses with exhaustion then jump on the animal and STRANGLE it
          </a>
         </h2>
         <a href="/news/article-9315971/Russian-snowmobile-riders-chase-pregnant-elk-jump-animal-STRANGLE-it.html">
          <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4099579433737502227/308x174_JPG_4099579433737502227.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="40" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4099579433737502227/636x382_JPG-HD_4099579433737502227.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="40" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4099579433737502227/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_4099579433737502227.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4099579433737502227/636x382_MP4_4099579433737502227.mp4" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="636"/>
          <noscript>
           <img height="382" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/4099579433737502227/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_4099579433737502227.jpg" width="636"/>
          </noscript>
         </a>
         <div class="articletext">
          <div>
           <p>
            WARNING: DISTRESSING CONTENT: Four Russians are under investigation after shocking footage of them 'pursuing and choking a pregnant elk' emerged online. The incident, which happened near the town of Vesyegonsk in western Russia on February 24, was filmed by one of the men's wives and uploaded to her Instagram account. The footage outraged internet users in Russia who reported it, prompting an investigation. Local animal rights activists said that the elk 'was a female and was pregnant' when it was killed. A criminal case for illegal hunting has been launched against the four. The defendants have been identified by their first names Yana, her husband Andrey and friends Artem and Mikhail. The suspects claim they 'wanted to help the elk after noticing it was limping.' They face up to five years in prison if found guilty of conducting an illegal hunt. The investigation continues.
           </p>
          </div>
         </div>

         <h2 class="linkro-darkred">
          <a href="/news/article-9315987/Impala-leaps-clear-snapping-crocodile-suddenly-pounces-watering-hole.html">
           Jaw-some escape! Impala leaps clear of snapping crocodile as it suddenly pounces out of watering hole
          </a>
         </h2>
         <a href="/news/article-9315987/Impala-leaps-clear-snapping-crocodile-suddenly-pounces-watering-hole.html">
          <img data-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/341704488270581097/308x174_JPG_341704488270581097.jpg" data-fps="7" data-frame-count="67" data-frame-height="184" data-frame-width="308" data-hd-film="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/341704488270581097/636x382_JPG-HD_341704488270581097.jpg" data-hd-fps="7" data-hd-frame-count="67" data-hd-frame-height="382" data-hd-frame-width="636" data-mol-fe-video-preview="" data-src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/341704488270581097/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_341704488270581097.jpg" data-video="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/341704488270581097/636x382_MP4_341704488270581097.mp4" height="382" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" width="636"/>
          <noscript>
           <img height="382" src="https://video.dailymail.co.uk/preview/mol/2021/03/02/341704488270581097/636x382_JPG-SINGLE_341704488270581097.jpg" width="636"/>
          </noscript>
         </a>
         <div class="articletext">
          <div>
           <p>
            Incredible footage from Luangwa National Park, Zambia, shows a female impala having a drink at a watering hole when seemingly out of nowhere, a 700lb Nile crocodile springs from beneath the surface. But the frightened impala notices the threat just in time, and is able to leap backwards and turn 180 degrees to avoid being clamped in between the crocodile's deadly jaws.
           </p>
          </div>

					message = 'We think our Android app is a much better way of viewing MailOnline. It\'s FREE in the Google Play store and has over 2 million downloads. Get it now! ';

					link = "https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.dailymail.online",
                    message =  "We think our Android tablet app is a much better way of viewing MailOnline. Available for FREE on Google Play. Download it now!";

				}

				var log;

					DM.setCookie(cName, cName, expireDate, "/");

					return DM.getCookie(cName);
				}

				if(cName && !getCookie()){
					var conf = confirm(message);
					
					if (conf){

						window.location = link;

				}
			
		});
